# NSManagedObjectContext.ScheduledTaskType.enqueued

**Case**

The enqueued scheduled task type.

## Declaration

```swift
case enqueued
```

## Discussion

Enqueued tasks execute asynchronously on the context’s queue. An enqueued task encapsulates an autorelease pool and a call to [doc://com.apple.coredata/documentation/CoreData/NSManagedObjectContext/processPendingChanges()], and its behavior is analogous to [doc://com.apple.coredata/documentation/CoreData/NSManagedObjectContext/perform(_:)]. The context’s queue executes tasks in the order you add them.

## Scheduled Task Types

- **NSManagedObjectContext.ScheduledTaskType.immediate**: The immediate scheduled task type.
